      • getConfig

        public KsqlConfig getConfig(boolean withOverridesApplied)
        Get the `KsqlConfig` instance, either with or without the overrides applied.

        Calling with withOverridesApplied of true will return the system config with the user's overrides applied. This is the more common case. This can be useful when the user should be able to influence how code executes by using `SET` to provide config overrides.

        Calling with withOverridesApplied of false will return the system config without any overrides. This can be useful if the users shouldn't be able to supply overrides to change the behaviour of the code you're passing the config to.

        Parameters:
        withOverridesApplied - flag to indicate if the user supplied overrides should be applied.
        Returns:
        the config.

      • getOverrides

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getOverrides()

        User supplied overrides, i.e. those provided in the request to the server.
